            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673977565672-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> brioche halves</strong> to the pan, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Set aside until serving and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673977569595-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673977569595-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673977569595-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673977569595-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673977569595-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, add them<strong> </strong>to a baking tray (reserve the bowl) and crush with the base of a mug to flatten them</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>a generous knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the tray and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 18-22 min or until the potatoes are crisp and golden – these are your <strong>smashed potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673977573503-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673977573503-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673977573503-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673977573503-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673977573503-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are in the oven, add the<strong> meat-free chick’n</strong> to the reserved bowl with the <strong>soy sauce</strong> then mix well until evenly coated</p><p>Combine the <strong>cornflour, ground paprika </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>in another bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>meat-free chick’n</strong> to the cornflour mixture and give everything a good mix up until the chick'n pieces are nicely coated – this is your <strong>coated meat-free chick’n</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673977577127-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673977577127-x400.jpg",
